HEADWORD: Crecy
<hw>Crecy</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the first decisive battle
of the Hundred Years' War; in 1346 the English under Edward III defeated
the French under King Philip of Valois.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> battle of Crecy.</syn>⟦br⟧
